<subSubSection pageId="128" pageNumber="129" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="128.[151,1436,1871,2005]" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">
Two species have been recognized based on genetic analyses, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Duvernoy" authorityYear="1851" box="[845,957,1873,1896]" class="Mammalia" family="Hyperoodontidae" genus="Berardius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cetacea" pageId="128" pageNumber="129" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="arnuxii">
<emphasis box="[845,957,1873,1896]" italics="true" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">B. arnuxii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Southern Hemisphere and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stejneger" authorityYear="1883" box="[1330,1436,1871,1896]" class="Mammalia" family="Hyperoodontidae" genus="Berardius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cetacea" pageId="128" pageNumber="129" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bairdii">
<emphasis box="[1330,1436,1871,1896]" italics="true" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">B. bairdii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the North Pacific Ocean (
<bibRefCitation author="Dalebout" box="[485,660,1908,1933]" firstAuthor="Dalebout" pageId="128" pageNumber="129" refId="ref98659" refString="Dalebout, M. L. (2002) Species identity, genetic diversity and molecular systematic relationships among the Ziphiidae (beaked whales). PhD Dissertation, University of Auckland, Auckland, 382 pp." type="book" year="2002">Dalebout 2002</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Dalebout" box="[675,921,1908,1933]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Dalebout" pageId="128" pageNumber="129" pagination="459 - 473" refId="ref98697" refString="Dalebout, M. L., Baker, C. S., Mead, J. G., Cockcroft, V. G. &amp; Yamada, T. K. (2004) A comprehensive and validated molecular taxonomy of beaked whales, Family Ziphiidae. Journal of Heredity, 95, 459 - 473. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / jhered / esh 054" type="journal article" year="2004">
Dalebout 
<emphasis box="[789,843,1908,1933]" italics="true" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">et al</emphasis>
. 2004
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Mead and Brownell" box="[944,1261,1908,1933]" firstAuthor="Mead" pageId="128" pageNumber="129" pagination="723 - 743" refId="ref113319" refString="Mead, J. G. &amp; Brownell Junior, R. L. (2005) Order Cetacea. In: Wilson D. E. &amp; Reeder, D. M. (Eds.), Mammal species of the world: a taxonomic and geographic reference. 3 rd Edition. The Johns Hopkins University Press, Baltimore, Maryland, pp. 723 - 743." type="book chapter" year="2005">Mead and Brownell (2005)</bibRefCitation>
suggested that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Duvernoy" authorityYear="1851" box="[151,262,1943,1968]" class="Mammalia" family="Hyperoodontidae" genus="Berardius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cetacea" pageId="128" pageNumber="129" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,262,1943,1968]" italics="true" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">Berardius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could be monotypic. A third and as yet unnamed species (informally known as ‘Karasu’) was described in 
<quantity box="[180,265,1980,2005]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.12064" pageId="128" pageNumber="129" unit="in" value="2016.0">2016 in</quantity>
the North Pacific (
<bibRefCitation author="Morin" box="[477,680,1980,2005]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Morin" pageId="128" pageNumber="129" pagination="96 - 111" refId="ref114636" refString="Morin, P. A., Baker, C., Brewer, R. S., Burdin, A. M., Dalebout, M. L. Dines, J. P., Fedutin, I., Filatova, O., Hoyt, E., Jung J., Lauf, M., Potter, C. W., Richard, G., Ridgway, M., Robertson, K. M. &amp; Wade, P. R. (2017) Genetic structure of the beaked whale genus Berardius in the North Pacific, with genetic evidence for a new species. Marine Mammal Science, 33, 96 - 111. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / mms. 12345" type="journal article" year="2017">
Morin 
<emphasis box="[556,612,1980,2005]" italics="true" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">et al.</emphasis>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
